Cooking Assistant
Cooking Assistant is a web-based application designed to make cooking easier and more enjoyable. Users can find recipes based on available ingredients, generate shopping lists, and plan their meals—all in a clean and modern interface.

Features
Basic Features

Recipe Finder: Enter ingredients you have at home to get recipe suggestions.
Shopping List Generator: Add missing ingredients directly to a shopping list.

Meal Planner: Plan meals for the week with organized recipes.

UI/UX Highlights
Clean, responsive design for easy navigation on desktop and mobile devices.
Dark and light themes can be added in future iterations.

Setup and Installation
Prerequisites
Python 3.7 or later installed.
Flask Python package:
pip install flask

File Structure
cooking_assistant/
├── app.py                  # Main Flask application
├── templates/              # HTML templates for the app
│   ├── index.html
│   ├── recipe_finder.html
│   ├── shopping_list.html
│   └── meal_planner.html
├── static/                 # Static assets (CSS, images, etc.)
│   ├── styles.css          # Custom styles for the app
└── README.md   # Documentation file


Running the App
Clone the repository or download the project files.

Navigate to the project directory:
cd cooking_assistant

Run the application:
python app.py
Open your browser and go to http://127.0.0.1:5000 to access the application.

How to Use

Home Page
Access the main features of the app via navigation links.

Recipe Finder
Enter a list of ingredients you have on hand.
Get a list of recipe suggestions, including any missing ingredients.

Shopping List
View and manage a pre-generated shopping list for your recipes.

Meal Planner
Get a weekly meal plan with recipes organized by day.

Technologies Used
Backend: Flask (Python)
Frontend: HTML5, CSS3
Styling: Custom CSS with responsive design principle
